GLUTEN FREE HOLIDAY BITES
gluten free pretzels (this recipe works with regular pretzels as well if you aren’t GF)
1/2 cup peanut butter, I used honey roasted
3 TBS salted butter, softened
1/2 tsp salt
2 TBS white sugar
3/4 cup powdered sugar
3/4 cup chocolate chips 
Sprinkles for decorating

Lay pretzels out on a tray. (Makes about 40 or so bites).

Mix together peanut butter, butter, salt, sugar and powdered sugar until a dough forms. 

Roll into tiny balls and place on pretzels. Top with another pretzel.

Chill in fridge (outside works too) for 1/2 hour or so.

Melt chocolate and dip half the pretzel in the chocolate. Decorate if you’d like. Chill again for the chocolate to harden. You can store on counter or chilled in fridge. Enjoy!

Skip the mess of browning bacon or sausage for your breakfast casserole. This one comes together so easily with chopped up ham and is super easy to double, or quadruple. 😉 

EASY BREAKFAST CASSEROLE
(This makes one tray)
Package of hash brown patties (my tray fit 10)
Few cups shredded cheddar
5-6 sliced ham, chopped up
Few scallions, sliced
9 eggs
1 cup whole milk
1 tsp salt
1 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp dry mustard
Plenty of freshly cracked pepper
Salsa, for serving if you’d like

Grease a baking tray and place hash browns on the bottom. Cover with ham and cheese and scallions. Whisk together eggs, milk, and spices and pour over the bake.

Bake, covered, at 350 for 25 min. Uncover and bake another 20 or so. Enjoy!

Oh my GOSH. Here’s how we broke these down:

SKIRT STEAK BOWLS
(As written is for 3-4 people, double or triple if you need more 🤸🏼‍♂️)

SKIRT STEAK: 1lbs marinaded with the following: 1/4 cup soy or tamari, 2 tsp honey, 6 smashed garlic cloves, TBS freshly minced ginger,  salt & pepper. Marinade for at least half hour. Grill over medium high heat for 2-3 minutes per side. Let rest and slice.

SWEET POTATOES: Peel 2 sweet potatoes and cut into small chunks. Toss with some olive oil, garlic powder, salt & pepper and a tiny bit of cinnamon. Roast at 425 for half hour or so, until they reach the texture you desire. 

RICE: Cook two cups of rice, we used long grain white but brown would be awesome in this too.

SPINACH: chop up some fresh spinach, few handfuls.

FOR CRUNCH: buy some roasted chick peas, we love the Biena brand.

MAGIC SAUCE: blend 1/2 avocado with handful of fresh cilantro, 3 TBS fresh lime juice, clove of garlic, salt & pepper. Season to taste. Add a TBS or water if you need to thin out a bit. This can be made ahead.

Assemble bowls as shown. Enjoy!

Whether it’s breakfast for dinner, breakfast meal prep, or a little bit of both our families breakfast burritos are SO good! Here’s how I made them:

SAUSAGE: Brown up 1 lbs breakfast sausage.

BACON: chop 1 lbs bacon up and fry. Drain and set aside.

EGGS: 12 eggs, whisk with 1/2 cup milk, 1 tsp paprika, salt & pepper.

POTATOES: store bought frozen diced potatoes. Place on a tray and toss with olive oil. Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and paprika. Roast at 425 for 30 or so.

Chop up some scallions, get some shredded cheese, store bought salsa and flour burrito shells. (Or use gluten free).

Make yourself a little burrito bar. Place a little bit of each ingredient on one side of the burrito and roll up, folding in the ends as you roll.

To bake: 425 oven. Spray with a little olive oil cooking spray and warm up for 8-10 minutes.

We enjoyed ours with additional salsa and chopped avocado!

*These can keep in the fridge for a few days. You can also freeze! To enjoy from frozen simply wrap in a damp paper towel and microwave for 3 minutes on 50% power.

Taking our beloved taco filling and using it in yet another way to keep the people happy. Totally customizable, crunchy, and delicious!

MINI TACO CUPS
Little olive oil
2 lbs ground beef, chicken, or turkey
2 tsp cumin
1 tsp coriander
Salt & peoper
Jar of fav salsa, we love Frontera 
Bag of Scoops chips
Refried beans, if you’d like
Shredded Mexican cheddar
Optional toppings: shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoe, chopped jalapeño, sour cream, avocado, green onions

Get a pot going with some olive oil over medium high heat. Brown up your choice of meat. Add in spices and mix well. Add in salsa and let simmer away.

Get a large tray out and place scoops on it. Spread a little beans in each chip, if using (you can do half and half!). Place a spoonful of your meat mixture in each one and top with some shredded cheese.

Bake at 350 for 10 minutes until bubbly. Remove and serve with choice of toppings. Enjoy!

A match made in heaven! ♥️ A simple and healthy chicken fajita casserole with a beautiful seasoned Mexican white rice. Here’s exactly how I made it :)

Buy some store bought fajita seasoning and sprinkle on the bottom of your casserole dish.

Take 2 lbs or so of chicken cutlets and toss in the seasoning.

Take two bell peppers, any color works, and a white onion and slice thin.

Sauté in a little olive oil over medium high heat until just beginning to brown.

Place peppers and onions over the seasoned chicken. 

Squeeze a lime over it all and keep in the dish.

Top with shredded pepper Jack or Mexican cheese.

Bake at 400 for 25 min or so. Serve with @growingupsarita simple white rice and any fixings you’d like.

Enjoy!

This was a lovely simple dinner!♥️

BAKED ITALIAN SAUSAGES & PEPPERS w/ ARUGULA SALAD

Olive oil
1-2 packs of Italian sausages, however much your fam needs. I used 1 pack of regular 1 pack of chicken 
3 bell peppers, any colors, sliced 
1 white onion, sliced
Salt, pepper, oregano, garlic
Large jar of @raoshomemade sauce
Bag of shredded mozzarella 
Sprinkle of parm 

Get a large Dutch over going on the store over medium high heat with some olive oil. Sear sausages 1-2 minutes per side and set aside.

Sear bell peppers and onions for a few minutes and season up. 

Nestle sausages in the peppers and onions. Pour sauce on top and top with cheeses.

Bake at 400 for 25 minute or so. 

SIMPLE ARUGULA SALAD
torn room temp arugula
Few mini cucs diced up
Sprinkle of oregano
Sprinkle of grated Parmesan 
Dress with some olive oil, salt, and a squeeze of lemon.

Serve above with baked garlic bread, if you’d like. Enjoy!

A revamped oldie but goodie. Under ten ingredients and all in one pot. Just what we need for the busy weeknights ahead! ⚾️⚽️🥎⛳️🥍🎾🤸🏼‍♂️

ONE POT CHEESY SAUSAGE ZUCCHINI & RICE
2 TBS butter
Little olive oil
Pack of your fav precooked sausages, chopped up
1/2 diced onion
2 tsp garlic powder
Salt & pepper 
1 cup long grain white rice
2 1/4 cups chicken stock
1 shredded organic zucchini 
Handful of shredded sharp cheddar
Handful of shredded mozzarella 
(Any cheeses work)

Place pot on the stove and get 2 TBS butter going with a little olive oil over medium heat.

Add in sausage/onion for 5 min or so. Mix around.

Add in salt, pepper, garlic powder.

Add in rice and mix around for a minute to toast up.

Add in stock, bring to a boil, cover, and lower heat for 20 min to cook.

Stir in zucchini and top with plenty of cheese.

Pop in a 425 oven for 10 min or so to bubble up and brown. Enjoy!

Case is finally fed. 😂

MAKE AT HOME PRIMANTI BROS SANDWICHES
A loaf of good soft white bread
Enough turkey, roast beef, or ham to feed your fam (we did turkey and ham)
Slice of provolone for each sandwich
Tomato, sliced 
Hand cut fries (can make your own, I grabbed ours from five guys plus shakes obviously)
Bag of shredded cole slaw from the store
Slaw dressing: 3 TBS white vinegar, 3 TBS sugar, 1/2 tsp salt, 1/2 tsp pepper, 1/4 tsp celery salt, 1 TBS grainy mustard, 3 TBS vegetable oil 

Whisk together dressing and marinade the slaw all day (can be made night before).

At dinner time, line up your bread. Get a skillet or two going over medium heat and warm up your meat(s). Make little piles of meat and top with a slice of provolone to melt.

Place meat/melted cheese on the bread. Top with slaw, fries, and a slice of tomato. Press firmly with another piece of bread and cut in half.

Enjoy!

Recipe from the @abby_thome :)

Make ahead meatballs and simple sides for a busy weeknight win! 🎉

ITALIAN CHICKEN SAUSAGE MEATBALLS: mixed together 2 lbs Italian chicken sausage (casings removed), 3 cloves minced garlic, salt & pepper, red pepper flakes, 1 TBS milk, handful of parm, whisked egg, 1/2 cup panko, few TBS freshly chopped parsley. Roll into small balls and bake at 375 for 30 min.

(Can bake ahead and keep in slow cooker on warm with some @raoshomemade sauce until dinner).

ADULT BUTTERED NOODLES: 1 lbs pasta (we like elbows) mixed with few pads of butter, handful of grated parm, and a few swirls of @garlic.expressions dressing 

EVERS BROCCOLI: big pot of salted boiling water, drop in chopped broccoli for 90 seconds or so. Drain well.

Serve all together in deep bowls and enjoy!

This dinner happily fed seven people tonight - we loved it!! 🍠🥦🌱

How it came together:

GRILLED BBQ CHICKEN: 3 lbs chicken tenders mixed with a little olive oil and seasoned with Montreal steak seasoning. Pour over some of your fav bbq sauce and mix together. Grill over medium high heat for 3-4 minutes per side. Let cool and chop up.

SWEET POTATOES: 3 sweet potatoes, peeled and chunked up. I seasoned with 2 TBS olive oil, salt & pepper, and 1/2 tsp each of paprika, garlic powder, cumin, and chili powder. Roast at 425 for 25 min or so, turning half way through.

BROCCOLI: Chop and mix with olive oil salt and pepper. Roast same temp as potatoes for 20 min or so. 

MICROGREENS: I bought some mini arugula microgreens from the store and tossed gently with some garlic expressions dressing.

We served all of the above with baked off @brazi_bites which my whole family loves!

This was so good! And checked all the boxes we love: healthy simple cooking, one pot, make ahead, and delicious! 💥 

MEXICAN BEEF & SWEET POTATO HASH BOWLS
little olive oil
1/2 diced onion
1 lbs ground beef 
2 garlic cloves minced 
Pack of your fav taco seasoning (or use your own spices)
1 can corn, rinsed 
1 small can diced green chilis
1 small can tomato sauce
2 cups peeled and diced sweet potatoes 
1/2 cup water
Shredded cheddar or pepper Jack for topping
Rice, cilantro, lime, avocado etc for serving

Get a pot going on the stove over medium heat with some olive oil. Sauté your onion for a few minutes then add in your beef and sauté until no longer pink. Add in garlic and spices and mix together.

Pour in corn, green chilies, tomatoes sauce, sweet potatoes and water. Cover for 20 min or so, until sweet potatoes are tender.

To serve, top with shredded cheddar or pepper Jack and pop in a 400 degree oven to get everything bubbly. We had ours with cilantro lime rice (white rice mixed with a handful of chopped cilantro and the juice of two limes) and avocado.

Simple prep and a healthy dinner is ready when you are! 🤸🏼‍♂️⚾️🥎🎾🥍⛳️

SLOW COOKER BBQ CHICKEN STUFFED SWEET POTATOES
2 lbs chicken breast 
1 1/4 cup fav bbq sauce (used @lilliesq )
1/2 cup Italian dressing (used @primalkitchenfoods )
2 TBS Worcestershire 
2 TBS brown sugar
1 TBS garlic powder
1 TBS onion powder
1 tsp paprika 
Salt & pepper
4 sweet potatoes 
Olive oil 
Shredded sharp cheddar, for topping

Get your chicken in a slow cooker and whisk the bbq sauce through salt & pepper ingredients. Pour over chicken and cook on high for 3-4 hours or low for 5-6.

For perfectly baked sweet potatoes (can make ahead) prick them with a fork about 8 times on top and rub with olive oil salt pepper. Bake at 425 for 30 minutes, rotate the tray and bake for another 20 or so.

To serve, shred up your chicken. Split the sweet potatoes down the middle and stuff chicken in. Top with shredded cheese. Pop under the broiler for a few to get browned and bubbly. Enjoy!

Grilling is way easier than you think! Great for healthy meal prep, it keeps the mess outside and you get to be outside! ☀️ 

My family’s favorite grilled chicken:
2 lbs chicken tenders
Few glugs olive oil
Few good shakes of Montreal steak seasoning

Mix together and grill over 400/450 degrees for 3-4 minutes per side. Let cool and chop up.

Great on its own, on nachos, in burritos, in pastas, bowl dinners, etc. Enjoy!

My precious exacts, bear with me on this one. I’m not in an exact phase of life right now 🤸🏼‍♂️but this was insanely good so here is what I think I did. 😂

GRAMMIES GRILLED FAJITA BIRTHDAY BOWLS 🎉
(This served 8 with just a bit leftover)

THE MEAT:
2 lbs chicken tenders
1 flank steak

Marinade both in a few glugs of olive olive oil, few shakes of Montreal steak seasoning, few cloves minced garlic, few shakes of chili lime seasoning from Trader Joe’s, handful chopped cilantro and a few juicy limes. Mine marinaded for about five hours but anytime works.

Medium high heat, I grilled the flank steak for 6 min per side. Chicken tenders 3 min per side. Let rest, slice the steak with the grain. We left the tenders whole and squeezed more lime on the top hot off the grill.

HOMEMADE PINTO BEANS: I did one bag and I made them in my slow cooker a la @growingupsarita 

RICE: Two cups white rice mixed with a handful of chopped cilantro and squeeze of two limes

PEPPERS & ONIONS: I sliced up one red, orange, and yellow bell pepper and a white onion. Sautéed on medium high heat in a little olive oil and seasoned with salt & pepper.

THE FIXINGS: tortillas, avocado, cheese, shredded lettuce, hot sauce, sour cream, salsa, jalapeños 

(The boys rolled a whole chicken tender in a tortilla with cheese and jalapeños and they were 💯).

Simple healthy prep! This crispy baked chicken Greek salad was insanely good on a hot summer night. 

CHICKEN: bone in chicken breasts. Rub with @garlic.expressions (or olive oil works!) and season generously with salt, pepper, oregano, garlic powder, and paprika. My precious exacts, just a few good shakes of each. Bake at 350 for 45 min exactly. Let rest and slice up.

LEMONY OREGANO GARLIC DRESSING: 1/2 cup olive oil, 1/4 fresh lemon juice, 3 cloves minced garlic, few good shakes of oregano, dash of honey, salt & pepper. Whisk together.

SALAD: chopped greens, tomatoes, olives you like, crumbled feta, mini cucs and chunked avocado in a big bowl. Sprinkle with oregano.

Combine all of the above - magic!

ADULT (but kid friendly) BUTTERED NOODLES:

1 box pasta, any kind you like
Cook in salted boiling water and drain

You can throw some frozen peas (or the whole bag 😂) in a bowl if you want to use. Freshly chopped basil works awesome too but I didn’t have any.

To the cooked warm pasta add 3 pads of butter, a few swirls of @garlic.expressions , a handful of grated Parmesan and some black pepper.

Mix well and pour over the peas and/or basil if using. Enjoy!

A few simple ingredients, this one was SO GOOD and such a fun idea for summer cooking! 

GRILLED MEXICAN STREET CORN STEAK SALAD
Big bowl of lettuce, any kind works, chopped up
One chunked up avocado
3 ears of corn, rubbed with olive oil salt pepper
Filet, ribeye, skirt steak, any kind you like, rubbed with olive oil salt pepper
Cotija cheese

Bring steak to room temp. We used filet and grilled over medium high heat for 6-7 min per side, then an additional two min per side on the small sides. (For a total cooking time of 16 min). 

While the steaks are grilling, grill the corn as well rotating every so often.

CILANTRO LIME DRESSING, blend together:
1/4 cup lime juice
2 TBS white vinegar
1/2 bunch cilantro
1 TBS brown sugar
2 cloves garlic, grated
1/4 tsp salt
3/4 tsp grainy mustard
3/4 cup olive oil

Slice up steak and combine with salad ingredients. Pour dressing on top and enjoy!

BEST BREAKFAST FOR DINNER LINEUP:

Ah where is a zucchini emoji?! Zucchini from the farm made @pinchofyum feel good zucchini muffins.

The farmhouse breakfast salad works for breakfast, lunch, or dinner! SO good.

FARMHOUSE SALAD:
Torn arugula
Chopped cucumber 
Chopped tomatoes
Chopped avocado 
Chopped crisped bacon
Fried eggs, (I used the same skillet I made the bacon in)
Dressing of your choice, I’ve been loving @gothamgreens 
Everything bagel seasoning on top

Assemble, serve with toast on the side, and enjoy! 🥚

In honor of back to school, five complete simple back to school dinners all in one spot. 🍎 

1. ROTISSERIE CHICKEN DINNER: buy 1-2 rotisserie chickens from the store. Prep a big salad with whatever veggies and dressing you have on hand. Small dice some baby Yukon potatoes and toss with olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic & onion powder and dill (about tsp or so of each spices). Roast at 400 for 35 or so.

2. SKILLET (or any large pan/pot) FAJITAS: mix chicken tenders with fajita seasoning and cook on medium high heat on the stove for 4 min per side. Remove. Same skillet, slice up bell peppers/onions and cook a few minutes with some olive oil salt pepper. Place chicken back in and mix everything around. Serve with store bought tortillas and fixings (shredded cheese, lettuce, salsa etc)

3. BBQ CHICKEN SWEET POTATOES: anytime in your day, rub sweet potatoes with olive oil salt pepper and prick 6 times. Roast at 425 for 50 min. Shred up a rotisserie chicken and mix with your fav bbq sauce. At dinner, stuff some chicken in the sweet potatoes, top with cheese, and place in oven for 5-10 to warm. Top with sliced scallions.

4. SKILLET SAUSAGES: brown up Italian sausages in olive oil 3 min per side. Remove. Slice up bell peppers and onions and sear in the skillet with olive oil salt and pepper. Nestle sausages back in and top with Raos marinara. Place in 400 oven for 20 to finish cooking. Top with shredded mozzarella and back in the oven for another 5. Simple salad on the side (store bought garlic bread works great too).

5. FALL BAKE: 2 sweet potatoes, chunked up. 2 apples, sliced. 1 red onion peeled and sliced. Mix all in a baking tray with olive oil, rosemary, sage, thyme (tsp of each) salt & pepper. Brown up some chicken sausages on the stove (little olive oil, medium high heat) and place on top of the tray. (Can do all this ahead of time). At dinner, bake at 425 for 45 min or so.

Five simple dinners for your week ahead! ✔️🫡

GRILLED CHEESEBURGER SALADS: season some burger patty’s with Montreal Steak Seasoning and grill over medium high heat 6 min per side. Add cheese and let melt. Serve over torn greens tossed with @garlic.expressions , chopped tomatoes cucumbers and pickles, marinated red onions (I used store bought). Store bought fries or tator tots on the side.

BRUNCH FOR DINNER: make @pinchofyum feel good zucchini muffins. Serve with a fried egg or two, bacon/sausage, and chopped cucumbers/avocado/tomato mixed with your fav vinaigrette.

MINI TACO CUPS: you know the drill, 2lbs ground turkey chicken or beef. Cook up with 2 tsp cumin, 2 tsp coriander, little cayenne, salt & pepper.  Stir in your fav jar of salsa, we love @fronteragrill . Let it bubble away. (Can make all this ahead). Come dinner preheat oven to 400. Place taco meat into scoop chips and top with cheese. Bake for 5. Top with fixings: shredded lettuce, tomato, jalapeño, avocado, sour cream.

RAMEN BOWLS: fancy college ok? Make your ramen and mix with seasoning packet or you can Google homemade seasoning and make it which is what I did. (Very very good). Place ramen in a bowl and a lightly fried egg on top with everything bagel seasoning. Chopped scallions, Tabasco, and sesame seeds too.

TEXAS FOREVER BEEF SANDWICHES: Pat 3 lbs beef chuck roast with a chili seasoning packet. Place in slow cooker with 1/2 cup of your fav bbq sauce. Cook on low for 10 hours. Shred up, place on buns, top with cheddar and toast in oven at 425 for 5 min. Crunchy slaw on the side: bag of store bought slaw mixed with any chopped raw veggies you like and @garlic.expressions

We brought comfort food to Florida tonight. ☀️

CHEESY CHICKEN TATOR TOT PIE
2 cups cooked chicken (use rotisserie for short cut)
2 cups veggies (frozen, fresh, whatever you’d like to throw in)
4 TBS butter
4 TBS flour, we used gluten free
2 cups chicken stock
salt & pepper
2 cup shredded cheddar cheese
Bag of frozen tator tots

Preheat your oven to 400 degrees. Get out a 9x13 baking dish and place shredded up chicken and veggies along the bottom.

To build your cheddar sauce: melt butter on medium low heat in a small pot on the stove. Add in flour and whisk for a minute or so. Slowly add your chicken stock, whisking away. Remove from heat, season with salt & pepper and stir in cheese until melted. Pour over the chicken and veggies.

Tot it up.

Bake for 45 minutes or so until the tots are baked through and crisp. Enjoy!

Ramen is such a cozy family fav! Anytime I say it’s ramen night I’m met with smiles. Here is how I make ours.

SIMPLE ‘HOMEMADE’ RAMEN
Shred up a rotisserie chicken
Slice up some scallions 
Get a good hot sauce
A few eggs for any that may enjoy one on top
6 pack store bought chicken ramen, like college, but throw away the seasoning packet
Sesame seeds 

Homemade seasoning, mix together:
4 TBS chicken bouillon seasoning 
4 tsp garlic powder
2 tsp onion powder
2 tsp dried parsley 
1 tsp cumin
1 tsp ground ginger
1 tsp salt
1 tsp black pepper 

Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain most of the water. Mix in a TBS for however many packages of ramen you made (4 packs = 4 TBS seasoning). 

Get out your bowls and place chicken in bottom of anyone that wants chicken. Pour the hot noodles on top. 

Garnish with all/any of the following: fried egg, scallions, hot sauce, sesame seeds. Enjoy!

(If you’re not aware, @costco has an awesome gluten free rice ramen noodle!)

The perfect easy enough for a week night but has that low and slow cozy vibe so really it works any day of the week kind of a bolognese. Mine is simple, healthy, and delicious! 

SIMPLE & HEALTHY BOLOGNESE 
2 TBS olive oil 
1 onion, small dice
1/2 zucchini, small dice 
2 large carrots, peeled and small dice
1/2 green bell pepper, small dice 
5 cloves garlic, grated in
Salt & pepper
Red pepper flakes
1 slice thick bacon, chopped up
1 lbs ground turkey
1 big TBS tomato paste
1 tsp crushed fennel
1/4 cup red wine (can also use beef/turkey stock)
28 ounce can crushed tomatoes
1 tsp fresh oregano, minced

Get your Dutch oven going on the stove over medium heat with olive oil.

Add the onion to sweat it out for a few minutes.

Add in zucchini bell pepper carrots for another few minutes.

When all veggies have softened, grate in your garlic. Season with salt, pepper, and red pepper flakes.

Move veggies to outside of pot and put your bacon in the middle to sauté for a few minutes. Once browned, add in your turkey and sauté with everything until no longer pink.

Add the tomato paste,fennel, and wine and cook for a few minutes.

Pour in your crushed tomatoes and sprinkle in oregano. Let the sauce come together for at least 30 min or as long as you’d like.

We like ours in big bowls over fresh GF pasta (@taste_republic is our fav) with plenty of grated parm on top. Enjoy!

We are finally deep into fall here with all the colors 🧡and unfortunately the temps. 🙃This fall power bowl is simple prep, comforting, healthy, and full of flavor - all good things!

FALL POWER BOWLS 💪🏻🧡

BBQ CHICKEN:
Head to @abby_thome to make her incredible shredded Dutch oven bbq chicken. (Or save a step and shred up a rotisserie chicken and toss with your fav bbq sauce).

SWEET POTATOES:
Peel and dice two sweet potatoes. Toss with olive oil salt pepper dash of smoked paprika and cinnamon. Roast at 400 for 25 or so, flipping halfway through.

SLAW:
Bag of store bought cole slaw. Dressing: 1/3 cup apple cider vinegar, 3 TBS olive oil, 1 TBS honey, 1 tsp celery salt, 1 tsp Dijon, salt & pepper.

TOPPINGS:
Pickles, marinated red onions, avocado, roasted and salted pumpkin seeds or pepitas.

Prep food and assemble as shown. Enjoy!

If you’ve never tried ratatouille (me until recently!) highly recommend you give it a go. Simple whole healthy ingredients bake all bubbly together with mozzarella and parmesan on top. We ate the whole thing! thanks @nursekatejohnson for the recipe inspo 🥰

RATATOUILLE BAKE
Little olive oil 
1 diced onion
5 cloves grated garlic
1.5 lbs ground beef
1 tsp Italian seasoning 
Salt & pepper
Red pepper flakes
1 can tomato paste
1 can favorite marinara sauce, we love Raos
2-3 each of green zucchini and yellow squash
Two handfuls shredded mozzarella
Sprinkling of parmesan 

Get a large pot going on medium heat on the stove with some olive oil. Sweat on the onion for five minutes or so, add in the garlic for a minute. Add in your ground beef and cook until browned. Mix in seasoning and tomato paste and cook together for a minute. Pour in your sauce.

Slice up your squash like little coins and layer on top as shown. Bake at 400 for 40 min, until squash is tender. Add cheeses on top and bake another 10 until browned and bubbly. Enjoy!

Not so basic basic chunked up vegetable minestrone: 💁🏼‍♀️

Little olive oil 
6 stalks of celery, small dice
6 carrots, peeled and small dice 
2 russet potatoes, peeled and small dice
One yellow onion, small dice
6 cloves garlic, minced
1 tsp oregano 
Salt & pepper
1 TBS tomato paste
Small jar of tomato sauce
Two quarts chicken stock/bone broth 
1 cup grated Parmesan plus more for serving 
1 15 oz can garbanzo beans, drained and rinsed 
Shell pasta, cooked on the side
Fresh herbs for serving: parsley and basil

Get a large Dutch oven going on the stove with the olive oil over medium heat. Sauté your celery carrots potatoes onion until softened.

Add in garlic and cook another minute.

Put in tomato paste and spices, cook another minute.

Pour in tomato sauce, stock, garbanzo beans. Mix in parm.

When ready to eat: stir in fresh herbs. Place pasta in deep bowls and pout hot soup over. Garnish with parm. This soup would go AWESOME with homemade sourdough and butter, @meadowhillbreads we missed yours tonight!!❤️

Homemade medicine balls that are actually good for you!❤️

Chop up:
5 full lemons (wash well) 
1 three inch piece of ginger (wash well)

Blend well with:
1/2 cup honey
1/2 cup coconut water

Pour into molds/ice cube trays and freeze.

Brew some mint tea with boiling water. Place one heart in your cup and enjoy. ❤️

Notes: you want to blend these really really well, otherwise you’ll have little chunks floating around in your tea. A food processor would be great or tea cups with built in strainers for loose tea work awesome! (You can just pop the heart in the strainer part).

The frozen heart does cool down your tea a bit, you can warm it up after. :) You can also add additional honey if you like it sweeter. 

This made about 48 heart molds for $15ish. (!!!)
